text: Hit is definitely one of the most difficult choreography of Seventeen. The way it's so fast paced and they are totally looking like one unit/entity is super cool. They totally deserve the title of synchronisation kings. Every member is so good that  all of them can pass off as the main dancer. The song is catchy. Jun's moves were so clean. I was totally gaping at Jeonghan and The8's individual parts. They were so fluid in their movements. The part where they  (Jeonghan and The8) sort of did a duet and then Jeonghan continued it with Seungkwan (I think) was so stunning. I absolutely love this performance. Seventeen for the win ❤

who did the legendary chorus the best.(my opinion) just an opinion. no judging.
1. Jun : You knew this coming right?. His was the most satisfying to watch.
2. Hoshi : As expected our main dancer and choreographer.
3. Dino : And our another main dancer.( it was really hard to choose between hoshi and dino.)
4. Woozi : He is already good at singing, producing and dancing. what this man cannot do?
5. Minghao: Our lead dancer did pretty good.
6. Vernon: He did it like it was nothing.
7. Wonwoo: I'm surprised he did really good.
8. Mingyu: It was not that bad.
9. Dokyeom: He was busy singing but still did very good.
10. Joshua: I like how he tried his best.
( Seungkwan was injured so he couldn't participated)

author: @xiumin6823
text:
*Appreciation Comment for Boo Seungkwan:*

Carats already have that habit to count all the members all the time to ensure all members are in the video. Because my love for Seungkwan is great, I noticed something.

You will notice from the start that he was not in the dancing, he only enters in his part which is a duet with Jeonghan and dance up until the before the 2nd Break dance start. You will noticed he exits naturally with the help of Vernon for him not to be caught exiting. And he enters again in 3:15 after the break dance with a jump for us not to notice him that much.

Because of his ankle injury he couldnt participate fully in the Choreo because it has lots of Jumping around and plus the hard footworks - but I am happy he is really working hard and devoted in what he wants.

Please appreciate our Boo more. He is more than just a comedian in the group. Thank you for reading ❤

Str3am Hit Carats! And give our boys what they deserve.

author: @ziiviolet
text: One of my favorite things about Seventeen is that they allow each member to be recognized for how great they are. It's very common in K-pop for a group to just have a "visual" or "center" and just make them the focus of every comeback. But seventeen allows different members to be showcased in different eras whether it be Hoshi during the clap era or Jun during Hit. I love it because ultimately it allows the group to feel like it's comprised of multiple individuals instead of just one individual and then "the rest". And you can tell based on how strong each members individual fandom is along with the overall Carat family. And for that I'm glad to be a Carat 😊!
